The Nucleus · node ATM · ATM · The dense core: protons and neutrons packed by the strong force into a ball ~100,000 times smaller than the atom, holding nearly all its mass at ~10¹⁷ kg/m³ (a sugar-cube of it would weigh ~billions of tonnes).

universe of origin : ATM · The Atom
seal               : ANCHORS THE ATOM and defines it. Its +Z charge holds the electron cloud; its proton/neutron count fixes the element and isotope; and it carries its OWN shell structure (see The Two Shell Systems).
